Package: roam
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, sudo
Pre-Depends: adduser
Description: Read-Only Access Mode - safe troubleshooting shell
 roam is a Linux security utility that starts a read-only troubleshooting
 shell under the dedicated roam user while a root-owned sidecar broker
 handles approved file edits, exec profiles, service actions, and
 optional sudo passthrough.
 .
 The session uses CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH to read protected files, Landlock
 LSM for write protection, blacklist overmounts for sensitive paths, and
 sudo session logging for audit.
 .
 Designed for safe troubleshooting on production servers where teams need
 to view logs and config files without risk of accidental modification.
